# Project Structure with shadcn/ui

## Current Structure
- **Main App**: [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Main application entry
- **Layout**: [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout component
- **Styles**: [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - Global styles and CSS variables

## Expected Structure After shadcn/ui Init
```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── layout.tsx
│   ├── page.tsx
│   └── globals.css (updated with CSS variables)
├── components/
│   └── ui/ (shadcn/ui components)
└── lib/
    └── utils.ts (utility functions including cn())
```

## File Purposes
- **components/ui/**: Auto-generated shadcn/ui components
- **lib/utils.ts**: Utility functions for class merging and helpers
- **components.json**: shadcn/ui configuration file (created after init)

## Development Workflow
1. Initialize shadcn/ui first: `npx shadcn@latest init`
2. Add components as needed: `npx shadcn@latest add [component]`
3. Import and use components in your pages/components
4. Customize styling through CSS variables in globals.css